        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-01-05T20:35:51Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Support Peaceful Protest Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires an individual who is convicted of a federal offense related to the individual's conduct (e.g., rioting) during the course of a protest to pay the cost of federal policing activity during the protest. In addition, such an individual is ineligible for pandemic unemployment assistance.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
